<plot>Based in current day America, INDECISION follows a short part of an assassin's life. The opening scene presents the main character in a room surrounded in darkness, this is the world of his own conscience. With just a picture of a man in an envelope and a gun on a table in front him, he contemplates on whether to kill the man, and is separated by his consciences, both DARK and LIGHT. The story follows the main character as he experiences indecision and conviction on his plan to kill the man in the picture. As the film leaves from his mind into the real world, the main character enters into two more dream states caused by the DARK and LIGHT sides of his conscience that influence what he will ultimately do.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?264142</url></doc>
